The hotel is located right on Venice Beach, which although I'm a fan of, it might be considered a little rough around the edges for some.	The hotel was clean, the AC was cold, the view of the boardwalk and ocean from the small outdoor space was fantastic.	Bring ear plugs, and watch for the shower water's changing temperatures, poor air circulation, and thin walls.	The hotel is in a sweet location, mere metres from the Venice boardwalk, it's also opposite a couple of the better restaurants around Venice Beach ( notably Danny's.)